<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-02-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/2–2845</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-02-28">February 28,
                                1945</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>I desire that you, as Secretary of State, assume the responsibility for
                            seeing that the conclusions, exclusive of course of military matters,
                            reached at the Crimea Conference, be carried forward. In so doing you
                            will, I know, wish to confer with other officials of this Government on
                            matters touching upon their respective fields. I will expect you to
                            report to me direct on the progress you are making in carrying the
                            Crimea decisions into effect in conjunction with our Allies.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>F[<hi rend="smallcaps">ranklin</hi>] D. R[<hi rend="smallcaps">oosevelt</hi>]</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>